SIMPLE: unkempt
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unkempt
<hw>Un*kempt"</hw> <pr>(?; 215)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>un-</ets> not + <ets>kempt</ets>, p. p. of <ets>kemb</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Not combed; disheveled; <as>as, an urchin with
<ex>unkempt</ex> hair</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.; Not smoothed; unpolished; rough.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My rhymes be rugged and <qex>unkempt</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unkennel</ent>⟦br⟧
